2017 WW13 Bakerville/SKX-D BKC Release Announcement (BKC #13)

\n \n \n

DEG Platform Integration Team

\n \n
\n

The DEG platform Integration team announces the release of 2017 WW13 Bakerville/SKX-D BKC release package for Intel internal use. The release is based on OS of\n \n ESXi6.5/\n \n RHEL7.3/\n \n WS2016\n server. The auto-installer packages are available in the Artifactory server (both SH site and OR site). Any questions please contact Bei, Ling.

Test Result:

l  Finish BKC test execution on RHEL7.3-BU2 , Windows2016 and VMware ESXi6.5. Please visit HPQC for test details. Refer to the installation\nguide for the BKC package installation

l  Bakerville(RP Board: Yuba\nCity RP fab3)

o   Total test cases: 137; Passed test\ncases is 132 and pass rate is 96.35%. 

o   Test coverage:  

    SKX-D ES2 SoC(QMXT, QMXS): Run P1 and P2 test cases, power cycling and Power & Performance test.

         SKX-D ES2 SoC(QN5Z): run boot up test.

HW rework:

    \n
  • No HW rework need for Yuba City\n fab3 board.

  • jumper setting refers to\n this link.

 Work\naround:

    \n
  • Secure Boot only can run in\n UEFI mode, so if we want secure boot can work and let bios load UEFI\n Oprom, we need Disable this option.
